{
  "id": "ash-chapel-breach",
  "name": "Ash Chapel Breach",
  "intro": "A ruined quarantine chapel on the old road to Hallowfen. The bells hang still, but someone has kept a fire inside, and the altar is not empty.",
  "briefingTitle": "FIELD WRIT OF THE ASHEN CENSURE",
  "briefing": [
    [
      "A hundred and thirty years ago the sky broke open and the damned came down with the wreckage.",
      "What the fires touched did not stay dead. It rose in the shape of Hell the way the old paintings always promised -- halos of bone, ribs like chapel doors, mouths full of borrowed scripture. The Remnant names it the Infernal Host. Most people just call it the Host, and bar their doors.",
      "The Bloom that followed should have ended the world. Then, for reasons no priest will explain and no scholar is permitted to, it stopped. The walls held. The bells still ring.",
      "No one is supposed to ask why it stopped. You learned not to a long time ago."
    ],
    [
      "The Holy Remnant feeds the cities, mans the walls, and rings the hours -- and in return it owns your faith, your confession, and your silence. It teaches that this is God's war, that the Host is Hell itself come to test the faithful, and that obedience is the only armor that holds.",
      "It also keeps a quieter office, the one the sermons never mention. You serve the Ashen Censure. You are a cult-breaker.",
      "When a chapel goes dark, when a town stops answering its bells, when someone starts teaching that the rot is holy, they send you to end it -- before it spreads, and before anyone starts asking the wrong kind of question."
    ],
    [
      "It is not holy work, and it has never once felt like saving anyone.",
      "You walk the ash roads. You find the cell. You put it down. You bury whoever the Censure sent with you last time, and you move on.",
      "You have done this for years. You are good at it. It has cost you more than you will ever say out loud."
    ],
    [
      "Lately there are more of them than there should be.",
      "The Choir of the Open Wound and a dozen smaller blasphemies are spreading faster than the Censure can burn them, in places quiet for generations. No one in the Office will say why. You have started to wonder if anyone knows -- or if they simply will not say.",
      "Your latest writ: a quarantine chapel on the old road to Hallowfen has gone silent. A Choir cell has nested inside. Clear it.",
      "You did not expect this one to be where the question finally started asking back."
    ]
  ],
  "width": 40,
  "height": 30,
  "tileSize": 64,
